casebody.data:
JACK W. MOORE v. STATE OF FLORIDA 11 So. (2nd) 486

January Term, 1943

January 22, 1943 Division B Merritt & Brown & Newberry, and Whit Newberry, for appellant. J. Tom Watson, Attorney General, and Woodrow M. Melvin, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. BUFORD, C. J.:

Appeal brings for review judgment of conviction.

The record has been examined in the light of briefs and argument of counsel.

The evidence is found to be entirely insufficient to establish the guilt of the appellant.

*296Judgment reversed.

So ordered.

BROWN, THOMAS and SEBRING, JJ., concur.
